tldr: The agent performed comprehensive browser and API testing of a sleep
  questionnaire application, identifying several working features and minor
  issues. It then proceeded to fix the identified issues, including updating the
  page title and committing various feature enhancements related to sleep
  analysis and reporting.
overview: The user initiated a request for thorough application testing,
  focusing on browser interactions. The agent systematically tested the sleep
  questionnaire application, covering the main questionnaire flow, form
  validation, report generation (including PDF download), and admin login
  functionality. During this process, the agent identified that core features
  like navigation, conditional fields, PDF generation, form validation, and API
  endpoints were working correctly. Minor issues were also noted, specifically
  ESLint/TypeScript warnings and an outdated page title. Following the testing,
  the agent proceeded to address these issues and implement several feature
  enhancements. This involved updating the application's metadata, adding new
  fields for pain and chronic fatigue screening, enhancing mental health
  questions, overhauling the sleep health analysis report, updating PDF
  generation, and adding mock data for new form fields. The changes were
  committed in logical, atomic groups using conventional commit messages.
